[361.647886, "i", "und(ciphertext, key5)\n    R2 = L3\n    L2 = R3 ^ f_function(R2 ^ key4)\n    return L2, R2\n\ndef attack(encrypt_fn):\n    \"\"\"Recover key[5] using brute force with fast validation\"\"\"\n    \n    # Collect plaintext-ciphertext pairs\n    pairs = []\n    for i in range(8):\n        p = i\n        c = encrypt_fn(p)\n        pairs.append((p, c))\n    \n    # Try all key[5] values\n    for seed5 in range(0x10000):\n        key5 = (seed5 * 1234567) & 0xFFFFFFFF\n        \n        # Decrypt last round for all pairs\n        states_after_round3 = []\n        for p, c in pairs:\n            L3, R3 = decrypt_last_round(c, key5)\n            states_after_round3.append((L3, R3))\n        \n        # Now try to find a key[4] that's consistent\n        # Use a fast check: try all key[4] values and see if any produces\n        # consistent results\n        \n        for seed4 in range(0x10000):\n            key4 = (seed4 * 1234567) & 0xFFFFFFFF\n            \n            # Decrypt round 3 for all pairs\n            states_after_round2 = []\n            for L"]
